 more than result in further actions by pyongyang while war is not in prospect he writes the possibility of military clashes cannot be excluded and the rising tensions are causing anxiety in the international community in an interview with yonhap news agency published in chosun ilbo shin forecasts a prolonged stalemate on the korean peninsula and the suspension of six party talks and other talks with the north gi wook shin interview in chosun ilbo in korean gi wook shin op ed in hankook ilbo in korean search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest north korea unlikely to give up nuclear weapons ksp in the news afp on november 16 2009 importance of us south korea relations in dealing with north korea ksp in the news korea times san francisco on september 25 2009 david straub joins clinton delegation to north korea to secure release of current tv journalists august 10 2009 fsi stanford shorenstein aparc ksp in the news north korea refuses to talk about the human right issues ksp in the news washington post on july 19 2009 us hopes to dissuade north korea from nuclear path ksp in the news voice of america on june 3 2009 commentary how to deal with north korea daniel c sneider mcclatchy newspapers on may 29 2009 support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
